**Describe the bug**
In certain places of the [CONTRIBUTING.rst](https://github.com/HBClab/NiBetaSeries/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.rst), there are references to the BIDS Starter Kit that suggest this repository _is_ the BIDS Starter Kit. These should be changed (but we should still refer to the BIDS Starter Kit since it is an awesome resource).

**To Reproduce**
Read [CONTRIBUTING.rst](https://github.com/HBClab/NiBetaSeries/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.rst)

**Expected behavior**
This is the NiBetaSeries Repository, references should be for the NiBetaSeries Repository.

**Describe the bug**
The readme.rst has several links that are not rendering correctly in [restructured text](http://docutils.sourceforge.net/docs/user/rst/quickref.html)

**To Reproduce**
Look at the [readme](https://github.com/HBClab/NiBetaSeries/blob/master/README.rst)

**Expected behavior**
The words should be hyperlinks and not links next to the words

**Desktop (please complete the following information):**
N/A

**nibetaseries version**
N/A

**How to fix**
change the links in [this line](https://github.com/HBClab/NiBetaSeries/edit/master/README.rst#L97)
specifically:
`contributing <https://nibetaseries.readthedocs.io/en/latest/contributing.html>` becomes
`contributing <https://nibetaseries.readthedocs.io/en/latest/contributing.html>`_

and `issues <https://github.com/HBClab/NiBetaSeries/issues>` becomes
`issues <https://github.com/HBClab/NiBetaSeries/issues>`_

(you add an underscore at the end)

body.35: Add visualizations of the connectivity matrix potentially as a circle graph with stronger connections between ROIs having thicker lines.
body.36: Currently, the `connectivity_wf` takes the mean of each roi to get a timeseries, may be useful to take either the first PCA component or a number of PCA components that explain 95% of the variance.
body.37: I have [generated test data](https://github.com/HBClab/NiBetaSeries/tree/master/data) to be included in a functional testing of the software
body.38: The [DerivativesDataSink](https://github.com/HBClab/NiBetaSeries/blob/7d8e4de484c93792e7cab41a2342ff93da09600f/src/nibetaseries/interfaces/bids.py#L38) interface currently is not connected to the main workflow, and thus no outputs are appearing where they should. It should be added after the `correlation_wf` outputs to the `output_node` in [base.py](https://github.com/HBClab/NiBetaSeries/blob/7d8e4de484c93792e7cab41a2342ff93da09600f/src/nibetaseries/workflows/base.py#L253)

body.44: I should conform the function names and doc strings to use one word or the other. It's typically considered more polite say participants, but bids uses the subject vernacular.
